  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is an increase in number of cases of Ebola since it first was confirmed in Nigeria in 22nd July 2014.   UNICEF will implement social mobilization as part of the WHO&#x2019;s and the Ministry of Health&#x2019;s containment strategy.  Using CERF funds, UNICEF will mobilize teams to go door to door for up to 3 months in affected areas to ensure that each household has knowledge about the signs and symptoms of EVD, transmission and IEC materials are explained and left behind for the family.</narrative>
  </description>
